social_posts.post_text: Thank you for letting me spend the past year on your wild ride, KB. #KB43VER
A few random snaps of KB on the set of #Electrikhana in Las Vegas last summer. #KB43ver

A couple years ago, when I first visited Ken’s ranch to shoot the launch of his signature wheel with Fuel Off-road, I never, ever anticipated eventually becoming his marketing director at Hoonigan Racing Division. 

Over the past year I was able to follow Ken around and capture his wild ideas—from driving his WRC race car through LA to building a private race course on his ranch (in the same spot that I had originally shot him with his signature wheel) and even being on set for the filming of Electrikhana and shuttling the Block family around Vegas. 

It was really difficult working for Ken and I struggled tremendously—not with him, but with how high and precise his expectations were, and his impatience for anything less than the best. It pushed me in ways that I had never experienced and he was teaching me to think like him (an award-winning marketing mogul) all along the way. 

While my tenure with KB was very brief, I think time will prove it to be of the most influential and impactful experiences of my life, and I will be forever grateful for it. #KB43ver

More progress on the #Touareg camping kit. This time I’m making panels for inside the spare tire cavity, where I will mount the @antigravitybatteries deep cycle, the water pump and @redarc_usa controller (thanks @tinyrigco!). 

The idea here is to make everything removable and relatively serviceable because there’s a solid chance I’ve fucked something up along the way so I want to be able to tear it apart and unfuck it.
I can’t even sometimes. #mayadogbins

Making this whole setup serviceable is crucial to me and my novice-to-intermediate levels of DC electrics, plumbing and general fabrication and carpentry. 

That means no self-tappers, irreversible glues or difficult-to-reach nuts and bolts—only threaded inserts and Rivnuts everywhere, with only two types of fasteners holding it all together. 

Now that the majority of the stuff under the false floor is sorted, next up will be everything above it, like the @dometic fridge, @sidio_design crates, @ironman4x4america slide and water tank, and a bunch of sitting and staring at the Touareg’s rear cabin space, trying to hypothesize all the ways @lindsayshair and I will use it. 

#touareg #tdi #vagoffroad #overland #camping #rtt #dometic #redarc #antigravitybatteries #plywood #osb #overlanding

Sometimes I use the #Touareg to camp with @lindsayshair, sometimes it’s a production vehicle for photo and video shoots. So the rear cabinet needed to be modular and not completely dedicated to camping. That’s where the @sidio_design crates come in. 

While the @dometic is a pretty universal tool in the kit, I wanted to be able to swap out the Sidio Crates depending on what I was doing and needed, the cabinet with hidden 10.5-gallon water tank was schemed up. I can have camping and cooking crates, recovery crates, camera crates and even a roadside tire swap crate with @pro_eagle trail jack, @powertankofficial minis and an impact gun, all interchanged and easily accessible. More on all that later. 

#overland #camping #carcamping #touaregtdi #vagoffroad #dometic #plywood #bedliner

Sometimes projects get sidetracked and this was one of those times. I wanted to make an access port for the electrical bits that is hidden under the fridge slide (when closed) and would allow me to check the charging and breaker/fuse status without disassembly. 

I plotted out the spot and cut the hole, then realized #marleycattigan snuck out the open gate. After finding him in a neighbor’s yard down the street and wrangling him back into his empire, I got back to work and forgot to keep recording the process. 

I ended up making a second port in the floor for the water connection and power switch, which will allow me to remove the false floor without disconnecting any plumbing or loosing pressure charge to the system too, but will cover that another time in another place.

Another amazing two days full of shooting rad cars owned by rad folks for an all-new VW/Audi calendar. 

Driving around the mid-Atlantic and woods of Jersey and Pennsylvania is giving me all the old feels and I love it. 

There’s still much more to come and a mountain of digital data to wade through to get this calendar thrown together, but every moment has been bliss so far. 

#morethanmore #carsandcameras #pvw #mk2gti #montanagreen #rootsclassic #zender #scirocco #mk3gti #vr6 #vrt

Another day, another shoot for @pvw_mag and/or the 2024 calendar, and another dog or three. I am really excited to be traveling up the east coast this week, shooting VWs and hanging with old homies. I wish I had done it earlier this year when my time was more fluid and free, but that’s life. I’m grateful for the freedom to do it now and the support of such great folks all along the way. 

I’ve spent a ton of time really dialing in the video rig for this type of workflow and capturing a ton of footage, and really look forward to sitting down and working through it over the next couple months, and hopefully planning a similar trip in the spring (in case I missed you this time!). There’s a ton of ideas on the table right now and I can’t wait to see what takes shape for the new year and share it with y’all. 

In the meantime, if you’re in Connecticut and free, come check out the @formulanonedriversclub season ender tomorrow morning at @twelve.percent.beer.project and maybe you’ll end up in front of my lens!
